
##not work

1. Install necessary packages for R Markdown: 
2. 
```sh
sudo apt install r-base
sudo apt install texlive-latex-base
sudo apt install texlive-latex-extra
sudo apt install texlive-extra-utils
sudo apt install texlive-fonts-extra
sudo apt install pandoc
```

2. Change R library installation path to `~/.local/R` to avoid permission issues: 

```sh
echo "R_LIBS_USER='~/.local/R/x86_64-pc-linux-gnu-library/3.6'" > ~/.Renviron
```
3.
```sh
sudo R
```
3.1
```r
dir.create(Sys.getenv("R_LIBS_USER"), recursive=TRUE)
.libPaths(Sys.getenv("R_LIBS_USER"))
```

3.2 Install R Mardown: 

```r
install.packages("rmarkdown")
rmarkdown::render("*.Rmd")
```

